{{Wireless embedded system |brand=D-Link |model=DI-524 |revision=G1 |fcc_date=07/13/2007 |is_manuf=No |manuf=AMIT |type=wireless router |fcc_id=KA2DI524G1 |pwr_v=7.5 |pwr_amp=1.5 |pwr_conn=barrel |cpu1_brand=AMRISC |cpu1_model=20100-G |wi1_chip1_brand=AMRISC |wi1_chip1_model=20100-G |wi1_chip2_brand=Airoha |wi1_chip2_model=AL2230 |wi1_802dot11_protocols=bg |wi1_ant_conn=RP-SMA |eth_cpu=true |sw_brand=D-Link |sw_model=DL1005E |lan_speed=100M |lan_ports=4 |wan_ports=1 |flags=schematics |802dot11_protocols=bg }} This model does not appear to have been distributed in the States.
The schematics state the switch is a IC+ IP175C. Pictures show a D-Link DL1005E, which may indeed be a rebranded IP175C or functionally identical. The schematics also state the RAM used as the '''ICSI''' IC42S16160-6TG (256Mbit) and the Flash used as the Spansion S29JL064H70TA100 (stated 32Mbit, 64Mbit actual).
